	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Thank You', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'Thank you for using WP Social SEO Booster. We hope you enjoy it as much as we do.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'We already added as much information as possible to each setting to make them easy to use. But to make it even easier for you to understand how to use the plugin, we created the manual below with some additional information where we thought it was needed.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Performance Settings', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'We included some of the recommended settings from the HTML5 Boilerplate and if you activate this option, then the plugin will automatically add them to your site\'s .htaccess file. We also included some more security settings to make your site a bit more secure. But that doesn\'t mean, that your site is now secure. These are just the beginnings and you should take some time to make your site secure. Hackers are everywhere and 3 out of 4 WordPress sites get hacked. If you want to learn more on how you can secure your site, we recommend that you check out the following site:', 'wpsseo' ); ?> <a href="//jvz1.com/c/22768/20094" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><?php esc_attr_e( 'WordPress Security for Webmasters', 'wpsseo' ); ?></a></p>

	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Open Graph Settings', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Info', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'We recommend that you fill out the information on the plugin settings page. These information will then be taken as default. With that you don\'t need to go and change all the written content. If the WP Social SEO Booster plugin can\'t find any information entered within the meta box, it will take the information from the settings page. These are also the information which will be used for the home page if you don\'t use a static page as your home page.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'Use the Open Graph settings the same way as you use the SEO settings for your site. Google and most other search engines do use the Open Graph meta tags for their listings too and MOST important, Facebook does use ONLY the Open Graph meta tags when a user likes your post/page/site. The better Open Graph meta tags you have the better it will look on Facebook and it can become much more viral.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'SEO Plugin Support', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'WP Social SEO Booster does support ANY SEO plugin for Wordpress and it does even support the SEO features from your theme if they are built in. The plugin will scan the code of your site and check if there are any SEO description and if it can find some, it will use it.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'With that feature, you don\'t need to go and edit any content at all. If you have proper SEO Title and SEO Description on your site, WP Social SEO Booster will use it for the Open Graph Meta tags as well as for the Google itemprop information.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Image Usage', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'The image is being used to post on the user\'s wall when he/she likes/shares your post. The plugin will use the images in the following order:', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'First it will check if you have entered an image in "Always Use This Image" within the plugin settings.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'If that is empty it will check if you uploaded an image in the "WP Social SEO Booster Open Graph Metabox".', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'If this is empty too it will check for a thumbnail (featured image).', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'If the featured image is emtpy the plugin will scan your content.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'If you\'re using an image within your content the plugin will use the first image found.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	- <?php esc_attr_e( 'If you don\'t use any images within your content, then the plugin will check if you have set a defualt image within the plugin settings page and if so, it will use that one.', 'wpsseo' ); ?>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Important', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'Default Open Graph Images need to be at least 200 x 200 pixels for Facebook to recognize them as significant objects for enhancing Facebook "EdgeRank".', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Google Authorship', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>
	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Info', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'WP Social SEO Booster will also add all the needed meta tags for the Google Authorship. This means, that you can have your picture beside the Search Engine listings as well as all other, by Google supported, meta tags such as Reviews, Product Offers, Business Listings, People, Recipes, Software, Videos and Events.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'After you integrated that in to your site, your listings can look like the one shown in the image below:', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Google Authorship" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/google_authorship.png" alt="Google Authorship" width="506" height="110" /></p>

	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'This is the listing for WP Social, where I added my Google+ profile to the site.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Important', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'Note that there is no guarantee that a Rich Snippet will be shown on actual search results and sometimes it can take quite a while until Google does display them. If it doesn\'t show up, then it\'s nothing wrong with the plugin and you will need to do more SEO for your site to get them shwoing up on your search engine listings. Also not all of the Rich Snippets do directly show up on search result pages. Some of them, such as Business, People &amp; Video will Google only use to better understand the content on your site. That doesn\'t mean that they won\'t have any affect for your site\'s ranking.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

