	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Setting Up Your Google+ Profile', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'If you have an account for Gmail, Google Docs, Google Webmaster Tools etc, then you already have the basics for a Google+ Profile. To get it ready for the Google authorship markup you need to have some specific data in your profile.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p>1. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Go and visit', 'wpsseo' ); ?> <a href="https://profiles.google.com/" target="_blank">https://profiles.google.com/</a><br />
	2. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Sign in to your Google account if you have one or create one.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	3. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Upload a Profile photo. This must be a clear facial, head shot photo. Cartoons, abstract arts etc aren\'t allowed.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	4. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Then click Continue until Finish appears, and then click Finish.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	5. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on Continue to Google+.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	6. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Then click on Profile (on the left hand side).', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	7. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Now click on the blue Edit Profile button at the top of the site.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	8. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on the +1 Tab and check the box "Show this tab on your profile" and click on the Save button.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Plus One" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/+1.png" alt="Plus One" width="355" height="123" /></p>

	<p>9. <?php esc_attr_e( 'After you saved the changes within the +1 Tab click on the "About" Tab and enter as many information as you like.
	The one you NEED to enter is the "Contributor to".', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Contributor" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/contributor.png" alt="Contributor" width="594" height="58" /></p>

	<p>10. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on it and then click on "Add custom link" and enter the Label and URL of your site and then click on save.
	You can add as many site as you like. Just repeat that step. Make sure that you enter the correct URL, which means if your site is domain.com and you enter www.domain.com, that won\'t work, because for Google these are two different sites. So with that said, if your site is domain.com then you need to enter domain.com.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	11. <?php esc_attr_e( 'After you added your site(s) click on "Done editing" at the top of the page.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Done" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/done.png" alt="Done" width="436" height="49" /></p>

	<p>12. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on the Profile button at the top left hand side and copy your Profile URL in to a notepad or other text editor file. The Profile URL should look similar to the one below:', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p>https://plus.google.com/u/0/104060139842691064332/posts</p>

	<p>13. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Now go back to the WordPress admin area and go to your profile, Users &gt; Your Profile', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Profile" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/yourprofile.png" alt="Profile" width="161" height="106" /></p>

	<p>14. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Scroll down the page and enter your Google+ Profile URL in to the given field.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Google Profile" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/google_profile.png" alt="Google Profile" width="562" height="48" /></p>

	<p>15. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Scroll to the bottom of your Profile page and click on "Update Profile".', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	16. <?php esc_attr_e( 'That\'s it. Your site is now ready for the Google+ Authorship Markup.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Homepage Settings', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'You have the ability to choose which author you want to show on your home page if you don\'t have a static home page. To do that, go to the plugins settings page. Scroll down to the Google Authorship Markup Settings and choose the author you want to use on the homepage. Make sure that this author has setup his profile, like we described above.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p><img title="Google Homepage Settings" src="<?php echo WPS_SEO_BOOSTER_URL; ?>includes/images/manual/google_settings.png" alt="Google Homepage Settings" width="600" /></p>

	<p><strong><?php esc_attr_e( 'Google Plus Publisher Markup', 'wpsseo' ); ?></strong></p>
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'With the Google+ markup you\'re not only limited to a personal profile. You can also add a Google +1 page to your site. The plugin will add the needed meta tag to the header\'s code automatically.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'If your site is a personal blog, then you can skip these steps. This is only for sites, who also have a Google Plus Publisher (Business) page and want to connect this business page with their site.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

	<p>1. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Go to your Google +1 page. If you don\'t have one you can create one. It\'s easy. Just follow the steps Google does provide and you\'re done within minutes.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	2. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Copy the URL of your Google +1 page and paste it in to the Google Plus Publisher field within the plugins settings page (Google Authorship Markup Settings) and save your changes. The URL of your Google +1 page should look like the following one:', 'wpsseo' ); ?> https://plus.google.com/105389611532237339285<br />
	3. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Go back to your Google +1 page and click on the blue "Edit profile" button at the top of the page.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	3. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Scroll down and go to the "About" tab.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	4. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on Website and add the URL of your site.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	5. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click save.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	6. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Now click on the gray "Link website" button next to the URL.', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	7. <?php esc_attr_e( 'A new window will popup. You don\'t need to enter any code in to your website. The plugin has done that for you. Just click on the blue "Test website" button and then click on "Done".', 'wpsseo' ); ?><br />
	8. <?php esc_attr_e( 'Click on "Done editing" at the top of the Google +1 page. That\'s it. Your site is ready.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>

