	<h2><?php esc_attr_e( 'Star Rating', 'wpsseo' ); ?></h2>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'We also included a star rating system in to the plugin which allows you to add the star rating to all your content. The star rating does also support the Google Rich Snippets Aggregate Rating. So when your visitors do rate your content, then this will show up on the search listings for your site.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'You also have the ability to display the rating stars using the following shortcode: [wps_ratings]. This will place the rating stars on the left hand side of the content. If you want to display it on the right hand side, use the following shortcode: [wps_ratings position="right"]. If you\'re using the shortcode, youu don\'t need to activate the rating for that post.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'To enable the star rating for individual posts, click on the "Choose Individual" link beside the content type you want the star rating being enabled. A pop up window with your content will show up, where you have the ability to choose on which of these entries you want to enable the star rating. To enable the star ratings for all entries within a content type, just click on the first checkbox which appears at the left of the content type.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'You also have the ability to enable the star ratings manually for each content you create.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
	<p><?php esc_attr_e( 'If you want to reset the star rating for your content, you can do that either within the settings page and do it for all entries within a content type, or choose individual entries to reset them. You also have the ability to reset the received ratings for each content, within the star rating meta box.', 'wpsseo' ); ?></p>
	
